# UI overlay animations

Use the project defaults below instead of instant show/hide or one-off keyframes.

## Floating popovers (Radix / shadcn)

Add class **`ui-popover-content`** to menu, dialog, or popover content roots.

- Styles live in `app/globals.css` (`ui-popover-in` / `ui-popover-out`).
- Already applied on `components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx` (`DropdownMenuContent`, `DropdownMenuSubContent`).
- Respects `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

## Inline expand (checkout panels)

Use **`OverlayReveal`** from `@/components/ui/overlay-reveal` for content that opens below a control (delivery date calendar, optional fields).

```tsx
<OverlayReveal open={isOpen} className="my-panel">
  {children}
</OverlayReveal>
```

- Global classes: `.ui-overlay-reveal` / `.ui-overlay-reveal--open` (grid `0fr` → `1fr`, fade, slight slide).
- Match spacing with a modifier when open, e.g. `margin-top` on `.my-panel.ui-overlay-reveal--open` (see `DeliveryDateSelector`).
- Do **not** conditionally mount with `{open && …}` only — that skips the close animation.

## Existing patterns

- Gift message chips: `co-gift-chips-reveal` in `PremiumCheckoutFlow` (same motion idea).
- LINE ID field: `LineIdFieldReveal` → wraps `OverlayReveal`.

## Tokens

`--ui-overlay-ease`, `--ui-overlay-expand-duration`, `--ui-popover-duration` in `:root` (`app/globals.css`).
